It might be helpful to ask someone, perhaps several people, who would seem to know, what are or are not safe activities in a particular area.  If you are staying in a hotel, for instance, you might ask the management where and when it is okay to walk or drive in the area. Even upscale parts of Johannesburg can be dangerous to drive through. As a general rule, to leave yourself an opening when traveling in traffic. If you are threatened or even feel that you will be, run a red light if it is your means of escape.

